title: The Searchers
overview: An American Civil War veteran embarks on a journey to rescue his niece from the Comanches.

title: The Treasure of the Sierra Madre
overview: Two Americans searching for work in Mexico convince an old prospector to help them mine for gold in the Sierra Madre Mountains.

title: Stagecoach
overview: A group of people traveling on a stagecoach find their journey complicated by the threat of Geronimo and learn something about each other in the process.

title: Children of Men
overview: In 2027, in a chaotic world in which women have become somehow infertile, a former activist agrees to help transport a miraculously pregnant woman to a sanctuary at sea.

title: Hunt for the Wilderpeople
overview: A national manhunt is ordered for a rebellious kid and his foster uncle who go missing in the wild New Zealand bush.

title: The Ten Commandments
overview: Moses, an Egyptian Prince, learns of his true heritage as a Hebrew and his divine mission as the deliverer of his people.

title: Inglourious Basterds
overview: In Nazi-occupied France during World War II, a plan to assassinate Nazi leaders by a group of Jewish U.S. soldiers coincides with a theatre owner's vengeful plans for the same.

title: Life of Pi
overview: A young man who survives a disaster at sea is hurtled into an epic journey of adventure and discovery. While cast away, he forms an unexpected connection with another survivor: a fearsome Bengal tiger.

title: Lawrence of Arabia
overview: The story of T.E. Lawrence, the English officer who successfully united and led the diverse, often warring, Arab tribes during World War I in order to fight the Turks.

title: Spartacus
overview: The slave Spartacus leads a violent revolt against the decadent Roman Republic.

title: Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas
overview: An oddball journalist and his psychopathic lawyer travel to Las Vegas for a series of psychedelic escapades.
stars: ['Johnny Depp', 'Benicio Del Toro', 'Tobey Maguire', 'Michael Lee Gogin']

title: Into the Wild
overview: After graduating from Emory University, top student and athlete Christopher McCandless abandons his possessions, gives his entire $24,000 savings account to charity and hitchhikes to Alaska to live in the wilderness. Along the way, Christopher encounters a series of characters that shape his life.

title: Lagaan: Once Upon a Time in India
overview: The people of a small village in Victorian India stake their future on a game of cricket against their ruthless British rulers.

title: Interstate 60: Episodes of the Road
overview: Neal Oliver, a very confused young man and an artist, takes a journey of a lifetime on a highway I60 that doesn't exist on any of the maps, going to the places he never even heard of, searching for an answer and his dreamgirl.

title: Fitzcarraldo
overview: The story of Brian Sweeney Fitzgerald, an extremely determined man who intends to build an opera house in the middle of a jungle.

title: Nebraska
overview: An aging, booze-addled father makes the trip from Montana to Nebraska with his estranged son in order to claim a million-dollar Mega Sweepstakes Marketing prize.

title: The Bridge on the River Kwai
overview: British POWs are forced to build a railway bridge across the river Kwai for their Japanese captors, not knowing that the allied forces are planning to destroy it.

title: Dead Man
overview: On the run after murdering a man, accountant William Blake encounters a strange aboriginal American man named Nobody who prepares him for his journey into the spiritual world.

title: Rio Bravo
overview: A small-town sheriff in the American West enlists the help of a cripple, a drunk, and a young gunfighter in his efforts to hold in jail the brother of the local bad guy.

title: Stand by Me
overview: After the death of one of his friends, a writer recounts a childhood journey with his friends to find the body of a missing boy.
